Package: noyalib
Architecture: any
Depends:
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends},
Description: Pure-Rust YAML 1.2 parser, formatter, and validator
 noyalib provides the `noyafmt` and `noyavalidate` command-line tools
 backed by a pure-Rust YAML 1.2 implementation with full serde
 integration and zero `unsafe` code.
 .
 noyafmt rewrites YAML files through a lossless CST formatter that
 preserves comments, anchor positions, and document structure
 byte-for-byte while normalising whitespace and quoting.
 noyavalidate checks YAML syntax and (optionally) enforces a JSON
 Schema 2020-12 contract.

Package: noyalib-dbgsym
Architecture: any
Section: debug
Priority: optional
Depends:
 noyalib (= ${binary:Version}),
 ${misc:Depends},
Description: Debug symbols for noyalib
 This package contains the debug symbols for the noyafmt and
 noyavalidate binaries shipped by the `noyalib` package.
 .
 Install when stack-unwinding tooling, profilers, or crash
 reporters need to resolve symbol names from production
 telemetry.
